You can deploy Kubernetes clusters to <%= vars.product_short %> directly in <%= vars.product_short %> Management Console.

1. Go to the **Enterprise PKS** view of the management console.
1. Select the **Clusters** tab and click **Create Cluster**.
    ![Create cluster](images/create-cluster.png)
    [View a larger version of this image](images/create-cluster.png)
1. Use the **Plan** drop-down menu to select one of the plans that were configured when during the deployment of <%= vars.product_short %> Management Console.

    The plan defines the set of resources that the Kubernetes cluster will use. A summary of the selected plan appears as you hover over each option.
    ![Select plan for cluster](images/select-plan.png)
    [View a larger version of this image](images/select-plan.png)
1. Enter a name and a host name for the cluster, and specify the number of worker nodes to create.
    ![Cluster name and hostname](images/configure-cluster.png)
    [View a larger version of this image](images/configure-cluster.png)
1. Use the Network Profile drop-down menu to select a network profile for the cluster to use.e cluster, and specify the number of worker nodes to create.
    ![Cluster name and hostname](images/select-network-profile.png)
    [View a larger version of this image](images/select-network-profile.png)

    Network profiles allow you to customize the networking for different types of Kubernetes cluster. A summary of the selected profile appears as you hover over each option. If you have not created any network profiles, you can use the default network profile. If you select the default network profile, <%= vars.product_short %> Management Console configures networking for you, based on the plan that you selected.
1. Click **Save** to deploy your cluster.

You can follow the progress of the deployment of your cluster in the **Clusters** tab.
    ![All clusters](images/summary-clusters.png)
    [View a larger version of this image](images/summary-clusters.png)